In England, in the seven days to 18 February, there were 69,092 new confirmed cases (122.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 February, there were 84,217 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 18% (15,125 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 23 February is 3,622,085 (6,435 cases per 100,000 population).
